    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8600 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - BUMPER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>BUMPER</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Bumper Removal</title>
            <para>The 8600 Series aerodynamic bumper is attached to the chassis bumper mounting brackets utilizing (4)
                four mounting bolts.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Beginning at the upper two bolts, loosen bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900811">Figure 11, Item 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen both lower bumper bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With an assistant supporting the bumper, remove the two remaining lower bolts. Remove
                    bumper.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900811" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900811.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Bumper Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOWER BOLT LOCATION (PASSENGER SIDE SHOWN)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. UPPER BUMPER MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Bumper Install</title>
            <para>Beginning at the upper bolt hole of the steel bumper:</para>
            <figure id="f0900812" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900812.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Bumper Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CROSS MEMBER BUMPER MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FRONT CROSS MEMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MEGA BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BUMPER SIDE EXTENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SIDE SECTION MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. BUMPER MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. BUMPER MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. BUMPER SIDE SECTION MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With an assistant, place bumper at front cross member, align bumper mounting holes with
                    mounting holes in cross member.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert bolts in the upper holes (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900812">Figure 12, Item 8</hotlnk>), one driver side, one passenger side. Hand
                    tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the lower bumper mounting holes and insert lower bolts, and hand tighten.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten bumper bolts to required torque value.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque bumper bolts to 50 to 55 lbf-ft. (68 to 75 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
